Name: font

Synopsis: Define font to be used for [text].

Syntax:

Types:

Function:
`FProperty font(str fname)`

Details:

Description:
Sets the font to be used for text.
See [fontNames] for a list of available fonts.

Examples:
<figure f1.png>
t1 = text("Rascal", font("Serif"), fontColor("Blue"));
render(t1);
</figure>
![font 1](f1.png)

<figure f2.png>
t2 = text("Rascal", font("Monospaced"), fontColor("Red"));
render(t2);
</figure>
![font 2](f2.png)

